manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: AMACOOL Personal fan with tripods is specially made for baby but also anyone. We invent this to meet baby and parents need in summer, indoors and outdoors. The 3 flexible legs (tripod) are sturdy built to hold the handle of strollers, wheelchairs, crib or anywhere you would place your baby, keep it cool and entertained. As we surveyed, many parents will sit their baby child on car seat on a ride, if it’s rear facing and the AC vent are not located at a good place, your child wont get much AC. There comes our baby fan, which can be attached on car headset, no matter your child is rear facing or forward facing, he/she will get cool breeze easily.

Our fan with 3 speeds for your needs, Speed 1 is comfortable, quiet and effective for child, while speed 2 (Medium) and Speed 3 (High) are strong for adult. The baby fan is with rechargeable battery included - Grade A 5000mah battery, lasts 20 hours if set at low speed for child, it’s enough for a day outing like a trip. If you take it out to park, zoo and Disney, we suggest you fully charge the fan and take a portable power bank as backup power source, which (even it’s with just 5V/1A output) can keep the fan running extra hours.

We spend so much on the tripod to make it multi-functional and useful. It can be used as handheld fan for game days for soccer, camping and other outdoors. It can sit at your bedroom, office table, grab at your poor or beach umbrella, you can also set it at your boat, golf cart, or treadmill in gym...it’s a magic fan and wait for you to explore more.
Package Included: Portable Stroller Fan, USB C Charging Cable, User Manual (AC ADAPTER NOT INCLUDED)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Everything you need in one package!
reviews.reviewText: There are so many awesome things about this fan it's hard to know where to start! It is light weight and travel size so it is easy to pack or carry with you anywhere plus it is cord and battery free so you just charge it up with a regular usb and your good to go for hours! There are even lights to signal how much battery life you have left so that you know when you need to recharge it. The flexible tripod gives the ability to use the fan literally anywhere, it doesn't have to be on a flat surface or table like other fans do although it can do that as well. You can even hang it upside down or angle it so that it's blowing right on you or right in the direction you want it to blow because the fan itself also spins 360° around. I was pleasantly surprised at how well the fan worked at cooling me down considering it's size! It has three fan speeds that all work great and it is considerably quiet. The highest speed has a little noise but it is barely noticable. An added bonus is that the fan has an LED light that has three levels of brightness. I have never seen a fan with a light before but it is very versatile. There's also a timer with three options if you want it to turn off on its own after a certain time. Overall I am really happy with this product it just covers so many bases and so many needs all in one package. I like to tie it up on my little table with my laptop so that while I do school work I have a breeze and a light (like the photos), or when I go on walks with my baby in the stroller and it's really hot I can hook it right on the stroller to keep my baby and myself cool. I would definitely recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cool Breeze for Little Ones - AMACOOL Baby Stroller Fan
reviews.reviewText: I'm delighted to share my positive experience with the AMACOOL Baby Stroller Fan, a battery-powered clip-on fan with a flexible tripod, providing a remarkable 20 hours of work time and earning it a well-deserved 4-star rating. Let me provide an overview: You're someone who values comfort and convenience during outdoor strolls with your little one, and this AMACOOL fan delivers a refreshing breeze with some notable features.The 20-hour work time is a standout feature, ensuring a reliable and extended cooling experience during your stroller outings. The flexibility of the tripod adds versatility, allowing you to adjust the fan to the perfect angle for optimal airflow. As someone who appreciates hands-on solutions for parenting, the convenience offered by this fan in keeping your baby cool is commendable.The clip-on design is practical, providing easy attachment to the stroller, ensuring a secure fit without any hassle. The fan's compact size and portability make it a valuable accessory for on-the-go parenting.However, while the fan performed admirably, a slight improvement in noise levels could enhance the overall experience, especially during moments when a quieter operation is preferred.In summary, the AMACOOL Baby Stroller Fan is a reliable companion for outdoor strolls, earning it a solid 4-star rating. For parents seeking a convenient and efficient solution to keep their little ones cool, this AMACOOL fan is a commendable choice, with the understanding that minor improvements in noise levels could further elevate the overall experience.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Life and marriage saver lol!
reviews.reviewText: This fan is wonderful and I finally found a solution to our nightly feud!!! I have night sweats and hot flashes and by hubby does his best to understand but he HATES having a fan blow across his face. But one fan on my nightstand wasn’t enough, you get it ladies, right? We would start with a fan on his bed stand blowing on me and as soon as I would fall asleep he would turn it, so when the first hot flash started, the first argument started and so ensued the nightly dance. You’d think they would understand more??? LOL! We looked for clip on fans but our upholstered headboard is too thick, I bought a neck fan, but that’s a pain in the middle of the night so the fight continued. I have three fans by my side and the air way down. Then my hubs found this! When he got it in he maneuvered it on our head board directly over my head! It has three speeds and swivels and tilts to adjust to whatever position I am sleeping in. We keep it plugged in so we never have to use the battery and it’s co compact it travels perfectly! It’s just enough noise for me, a small peaceful hummm. It also has a light so I can read by it with fan off it he wants to sleep and I’m still awake (me a pause again)! It’s perfect! I also use during the day reading. I recently had surgery and the fan was again a life saver as I was bedridden for a week! I can’t say enough about this. I have gotten to where I just keep it on at night. The ONLY negative I can say is the little green power light when on. I did have to put some electricians tape over front of fan in small area to keep light out of my eyes at night when I’m sleeping but it didn’t affect the fan at all. I would recommend this fan 100% I’m sure you could use it about anywhere!
